physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Obtunded but responsive to voice, oriented to name; suggested papilledema in right eye; pupils round and equal, constricted from 5 mm to 2 mm; full eye movements; suppressed corneal reflexes bilaterally; no facial asymmetry; vigorous and symmetric movement of arms and legs; appropriate withdrawal to noxious stimuli; deep tendon reflexes 1+, symmetric responses; bilateral extensor plantar response (Babinski's reflex present).
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Mental status returned to normal over the next several hours after administration of Phenytoin.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Postoperative MRI showed a small amount of residual disease without enhancement or characteristics of malignancy on magnetic resonance spectroscopy.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Initial high-grade component was no longer present.
